						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records the construction of kitchen <hi rend="italic">(maḍappaḷḷi)</hi> and <hi rend="italic">yāgaśālai</hi> before the shrine Tiruvuḍaitāyi-Ammaṉ in the temple complex of Tirumaṇgīśvaram at Mēlaiyūr located to the west of Vallūr, built by merchant Tummiṇikumāraṉ, the son of Tummuni, who belonged to the Kaṇṇandai-mahārishigōtram of Periyapāḷaiyam.</p>						

